HEADWORD: Fleam
<hw>Fleam</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>flamme</ets>,
OF. <ets>flieme</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>flevotomum</ets>,
<ets>phlebotomum</ets>; cf. D. <ets>vlijm</ets>. See
<er>Phlebotomy</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg. & Far.)</fld> <def>A sharp
instrument used for opening veins, lancing gums, etc.; a kind of
lancet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fleam tooth</b></col>, <cd>a tooth of a saw shaped like
an isosceles triangle; a peg tooth.</cd>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fleamy</ent>⟦br⟧
